  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Adult subjects 18 years of age and older who are scheduled for polysomnography (PSG),
        regardless of final diagnosis AND adult subjects who have already been diagnosed with OSA
        based on a prior PSG and are already on treatment. OSA diagnosis will be defined as an
        apnea/hypopnea index (AHI) &gt;or =5 episodes per hour.
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

        We will recruit subjects who are:

          -  18 years of age and older.

          -  Willing and able to give informed consent

        AND any of the following:

          -  PSG (polysomnogram)requested by a physician based on clinical grounds

          -  AHI (Apnea-hypopnea index) â‰¥ 5 episodes per hour based on a prior PSG.

        Exclusion Criteria:

        Incapable of giving informed consent

          -  Under the age of 18
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
